# https://github.com/browserslist/browserslist#readme
#
# Minimum baseline: ES2020 (optional chaining `?.` / nullish coalescing `??`).
# The floor is kept at/above ES2020 so bundled npm deps that ship ES2020 syntax
# untranspiled (e.g. @sentry/browser 9.x) still parse natively — Babel does not
# transpile node_modules. Enforced at build time by `npm run check:syntax`.
#
# Explicit version floors only: share-based / `last N` queries are intentionally
# omitted because they can silently re-admit a sub-ES2020 browser and reintroduce
# syntax-error breakage. Android Chrome / Firefox are evergreen and covered.
Chrome >= 80
Edge >= 80
Firefox >= 74
Safari >= 13.1
iOS >= 13.4
Samsung >= 13
